  "description": "<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p1069260/\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_shuangyu.gif\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a><br /><p>\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2017/02/26/5165207912027fb192b297d28c340803.jpg\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t在前篇中，小编已经为大家讲解过：在英语中，一些动词的过去分词可以转化成形容词，在句子中可以充当修饰语、主语补语以及宾语补语。我们不妨称这类词为&ldquo;<span style=\"color: #f00;\">形容词化的过去分词</span>&rdquo;。</p>\n<p>\n\t那么，这类过去分词可以用作哪些动词的宾语补语？</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"color: #f00;\"><strong>一、表示感觉和心理状态的动词，如see, hear, feel，find等等。</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;The teacher saw the students assembled in the playground.</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;老师看到学生在操场集合。</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;I found my old friend greatly changed.</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;我发现老朋友大变样。</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"color: #f00;\"><strong>二、表示&ldquo;致使&rdquo;意义的动词，如：make, get, have, keep等等。</strong></span></p>\n<p align=\"justify\">\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;My brother finally had his long hair cut yesterday.</p>\n<p align=\"justify\">\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;我哥哥昨天终于把他的长发剪掉了。</p>\n<p align=\"justify\">\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;Our teacher is trying to make us understood.</p>\n<p align=\"justify\">\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;老师正努力让我们弄明白。</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"color: #f00;\"><strong>三、表示希望、要求、命令等意义的动词，如like, want, wish, order等等。</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;We wish this wonderful film continued.</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;我们希望这部精彩的电影有后续。</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;My parents won&rsquo;t want me involved in such thing.</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;我父母不想我卷入这种事情中。</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;以上三类动词都可以接&ldquo;形容词化的过去分词&rdquo;作宾语补语，你都get到了吗？</p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p1069260/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p1069260\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px